Emirates has temporarily suspended all flights to and from South Africa from Saturday, 16 January, until 28 January. eNCA reporter, Heidi Giokos shares more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Emirates has temporarily suspended all flights to and from South Africa from 14 -28 January. The last flights out of South Africa will be on Thursday and the last flight into the country from Dubai will be on Friday. READ: Level 3 curfew: No more flights after 9pm The airline says this is due to operational reasons. Emirates says tickets for dates during the suspension will not be accepted and that customers should contact its offices or travel agencies for rebooking options.  Update: Emirates last flight out of South Africa will now be today the 14th of January and 15th of January out of Dubai. https://t.co/bXMsjGD860